 out. \r\n\r\nNoted was the fact that when there was no power from mains the battery was drained and died, when the power came back, as erratic as it is, there was not battery to absorb the power surges and hence the power regulator blew. \r\n\r\nRecommended is sourcing power from a different classroom that has reliable and less faulty mains. This will require a long extension cable.\r\n\r\nThe middle section of the wind mast is slightly bent. \r\n\r\nLeft the station fully operational and this job can be closed.   ','2015-06-26','Sisa Fihlani','OPS Regional Office','2015-06-11 09:19:39',''),(349,'AWS','No connection to the station. ','2015-06-12 10:25:04','Port St Johns','RM','New','completed',0,'Sisa.Fihlani','YES','2015-06-12 10:29:46','Request vehicle to travel and visit the station. Check the IP address written on the sim card and verify simcard and modem details. Check the motherboard for GPRS settings. Do the conformance. ','NO','closed','2015-06-25','yes','On arrival the station was fully operational but the office could not connect to the station. The motherboard was not converted to be compatible with GPRS communication. GPRS conversion was done and the verification of simcard details and the IP address was done. The office managed to connect to the station and download data after it was converted to GPRS.\r\n\r\nThe power from mains checked ok, battery charge rate checked ok, power regulator checked ok. Then readings from sensors were compared with travelling standards and checked ok but the full comparison check for conformance could not be completed because the office where the box is housed was closing for the staff knock-off time.\r\nThe station is fully operational and downloading data. \r\nNB! The box is currently on the floor inside one of the offices and a small table is needed to avoid damage to the box due to bumping.\r\nFurthermore, the station was temporarily closed for more than 2 years before it was re-openned in February 2015. All sensors must therefore be verified, change the wind sensor, verify rain gauge, verify pressure sensor and verify temp/hum sensor.  ','2015-06-26','Sisa Fihlani','OPS Regional Office','2015-06-12 10:25:29',''),(350,'RADAR','Radar off due to Genset error after running out of diesel during loadshedding. The Genset needs to be reset (and then put into manual mode) and then the radar needs to be restarted. Diesel needs to be purchased urgently.','2015-06-15 09:53:03','East London','RM','New','completed',0,'Donald.Muller','YES','2015-06-15 09:54:43','Will attend to the fault today 15th June','NO','closed','2015-06-22','yes','Reset Genset, and then put into OFF mode. Restarted radar','2015-06-22','donald muller','OPS Technical','2015-06-15 09:53:20',''),(352,'AWS','90 day conformance is due.','2015-06-17 15:42:20','Fort Beaufort','PM','New','completed',0,'Lungile.Jele','YES','2015-06-18 09:25:20','90 day conformance','YES','closed','2015-06-18','yes','90 day conformance carried out. AWS working well.','2015-06-22','Brent','OPS Technical','2015-06-18 09:24:58',''),(353,'RADAR','Fit new batteries for UPS, Repair faulty air-con fan, Top-up diesel, Install new Azimuth/Elevation grease, drain and install new Azimuth gearbox oil.','2015-06-22 09:32:35','East London','RM','New','completed',0,'Donald.Muller','YES','2015-06-22 09:33:50','Attend to job from the 23rd June','NO','closed','2015-08-03','yes','Fitted new UPS batteries. Topped up diesel. Removed broken Aircon fan and fitted fan from faulty aircon.','2015-08-04','donald muller','OPS Technical','2015-06-22 09:33:17',''),(354,'ARS','Battery dropped in voltage after a cloudy and rainy period. Modem lost it\'s setup.','2015-06-22 10:58:53','Elands River','RM','New','completed',0,'Brent.Appel','YES','2015-06-22 11:00:19','New battery Lead crystal will be installed. a new modem will be installed. 90 day conformance will be carried out.','YES','closed','2015-06-22','yes','New battery installed and a new modem. 90 day conformance carried o